<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Quercus</i> <i>durata</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>glandulosa</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>glauca</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>pungens</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>viscida</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>jepsonii</i>, <i>Cercocarpus</i> <i>montanus</i>, <i>Eriodictyon</i> <i>californicum</i>, <i>Fremontodendron</i> <i>californicum</i>, <i>Garrya</i> <i>congdonii</i>, <i>Heteromeles</i> <i>arbutifolia</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>berberidifolia</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>wislizeni</i> and <i>Umbellularia</i> <i>californica</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Hesperocyparis</i> <i>macnabiana</i>, <i>Hesperocyparis</i> <i>sargentii</i>, <i>Juniperus</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>attenuata</i> or <i>Pinus</i> <i>sabiniana</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 3 m; canopy is open to continuous. Herbaceous layer is sparse to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Quercus durata</i> > 30% relative cover in the shrub canopy as a dominant or co-dominant (Evens and San 2004, Evens et al. 2006).</li>
		
		<li><i>Quercus durata</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003a).</li>
		
		<li><i>Quercus durata</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy, or > 30% relative cover with <i>Adenostoma fasciculatum, Arctostaphylos glandulosa</i> or <i>Ceanothus jepsonii</i> on ultramafic soils (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Varied topography. Soils are shallow, rocky, and derived from ultramafic substrates.  </div>
</div>

        
