<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Quercus durata </i>sprouts rapidly following fire, and <i>Ceanothus cuneatus </i>and <i>C. jepsonii </i>seeds germinate from the seed bank. Safford and Harrison (2004) found that few species on serpentine depended on fire for germination. In contrast, many of the shrubs and herbs on sandstone are fire obligates. Fires are more frequent, severe, and uniform on sandstone than serpentine substrates.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (30-100+ years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
